Five students of the Police Academy Wudil, Kano and two other passengers lost their lives on Sunday in a ghastly motor accident along Kano-Zaria express road. The students were said to be on their way home after a semester break when the Golf model car they were travelling in had a head-on collision with a J5 model bus. Eye witness account revealed that both vehicles were engulfed in flame after the collision which led to the death of seven people including the five students. Four of the students were male and they are residents of Zaria, while the fifth one was a female and a resident of Abuja.